+ negative margin-bottom offsets border-bottom from grid gap\n    28→- .status uses modifier classes .connected (green: #ecfdf3/#a6f4c5/#027a48) and .error (red: #fef3f2/#f9d3d0/--danger) — setStatus(text, state) manages class swap; error palette reuses .message.error values for system consistency\n    29→- .message uses animation: fade-in 0.25s ease-out both — @keyframes fade-in defined in styles.css; fill-mode `both` ensures opacity:0 pre-start and opacity:1 post-end; translateY(4px)→0 adds subtle depth\n    30→- .char-counter uses classList.toggle('warning', len >= threshold) on wrapper div — warning class at 80% of CHAR_LIMIT (6400/8000); updateCharCounter() called on input event and after submit clears chatInput\n    31→- .output-box uses modifier classes .error (red: #fef3f2/#f9d3d0/--danger) and .exit-error (amber: #fffbf0/#fde8bb/--warning) — always classList.remove() both classes before each exec run to reset state; toggle .error on stderrOutput when stderr non-empty; toggle .exit-error on exitCodeOutput when exitCode !== 0\n    32→- CSS breakpoints: 900px collapses .dashboard-grid + .form-grid to 1fr; 600px mobile breakpoint adds flex-wrap on .app-header, collapses .exec-form to 1fr, reduces .panel/.sub-panel padding (14px→10px), .app-shell padding (20px→12px), .chat-messages max-height (62vh→50vh); .status gets max-width+text-overflow:ellipsis at 600px to prevent header overflow\n    33→- Dark mode via @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) in styles.css — overrides :root CSS vars (--bg/#111827, --panel/#1f2937, --line/#374151, --text/#f9fafb, --muted/#9ca3af, --primary/#5b8df8, --danger/#f87171, --warning/#f59e0b, --chat-user/#1e3a5f, --chat-assistant/#263144); hardcoded #fff backgrounds (input/textarea/.chat-messages/.output-box/.screenshot-image) overridden to var(--panel); modifier classes (.status.connected/.status.error/.message.error/.output-box.error/.output-box.exit-error) get dedicated dark-palette overrides; :root color-scheme is `light dark`\n   